All 7 user stories implemented. Here's a summary of what was built:

**Terminal UI (`hive ui`)** — A full interactive dashboard using ink 6 + React 19:

- **Header** — Session name, running agent count, total spend
- **Cost Bar** — Progress bar with color-coded budget tracking and per-agent breakdown  
- **Status Panel** — Live agent table (polls every 3s) with status, spend, last activity
- **Chat Panel** — Real-time message viewer with file watching, auto-scroll, role/type filters
- **Input Bar** — Dispatch messages with tab-completion, `/from`/`/warn` prefix commands, history recall
- **Agent Detail** — Drill into any agent to see git info, recent commits, messages
- **Help Overlay** — `?` shows all vim-style keybindings
- **Keyboard Navigation** — `j`/`k` select, `Tab` cycles panels, `1`/`2`/`3` jump, `d` dispatch, `q` quit

Quality gates all pass: typecheck clean, 67/67 tests pass, build succeeds.

